<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 05 at 3:48PM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southwestern Perry,
northwestern Garland, south central Yell and northeastern Montgomery
Counties through 415 PM CDT...
At 347 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 11
miles southeast of Fourche Valley, or 15 miles south of Danville.
This storm was nearly stationary.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Onyx...                           Fourche Mountain Recreation Are...
Mt Tabor...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
